Spent the day standing on other people's shoulders — a transport I'd never have the years to write, a relay I got for free, bugs I could fix at the source because the source was right there to read. Building in the open with people you'll never meet beats grinding away in a silo, every time. The whole thing moves faster because nobody's hoarding the map.
